Recommended Compilation Directions

Rust mainline
-------------

KindleTool uses Rust 2024 with an MSRV of 1.85. The mainline build has no external C library
dependencies. From the repository root:

	cargo build --release --locked
	cargo test --workspace --locked
	cargo fmt --all -- --check
	cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets --locked -- -D warnings

The release executable is target/release/kindletool (kindletool.exe on Windows). The root Makefile
provides equivalent entry points:

	make             Release build
	make debug       Development build
	make test        Workspace tests
	make check       Formatting, Clippy, and tests
	make install     Install the Rust CLI with Cargo

Release CI publishes Windows x64, Linux x64 musl, macOS x64, and macOS ARM64 executables. Kindle
ARM targets are intentionally outside this desktop release.

Legacy C oracle
---------------

The C 1.6.6 implementation remains available for compatibility verification. It requires nettle,
libarchive >= 3.0.3 with gzip support, and zlib. Build it explicitly with:

	make legacy

Other preserved targets are legacy-kindle, legacy-mingw, legacy-debug, legacy-strip,
legacy-clean, legacy-install, and legacy-format.

For a native Visual Studio 2022 build, install libarchive, nettle, gmp, and zlib through vcpkg,
set VCPKG_ROOT, then run:

	cmake --preset vs2022-x64
	cmake --build --preset vs2022-x64-release

The native C executable is written to out/build/vs2022-x64/Release. The older static-build and
cross-compilation helpers under tools/ continue to target the legacy C implementation.
